Six steps to focus on for this upcoming year..

1. Identify and accept where you are. Take stock of your current situation and accept it as it is.

2. Set achievable goals. Make a plan for what you want to achieve and break it down into achievable and measurable goals.

3. Take action. Commit to taking regular and consistent action towards achieving your goals, no matter how small.

4. Stay motivated. Find ways to stay motivated and remind yourself of the progress you have made.

5. Persevere. Don’t give up when things get difficult or challenging. Learn from your mistakes and keep pushing forward.

6. Celebrate your successes. Acknowledge and celebrate each step forward, no matter how small.

The goal has always been to improve and grow. This can be achieved by setting goals and objectives, learning from mistakes, and striving to reach new heights each and every year.

ingredients
Zucchini
Garlic cloves
Italian
Seasoning
Flatbreads 
Garlic Powder 
Cream Cheese 
Shredded
Mozzarella 
Directions
-preheat oven to 450 degrees. 
-Cut zucchini 
-Peel garlic; place cloves in the center of a small piece of foil. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
-Cut tomato lengthwise
-place zucchini on a baking sheet add a little of oil
-Place garlic foil packet on same sheet. Roast on top rack until zucchini is browned and tender and garlic is soft
While that’s cooking…
-place tomato in a medium bowl and toss with 1 tsp Italian Seasoning salt, and pepper; set aside.
-Once zucchini is soft, mix it in a  bowl with tomato; toss to combine. 
-Place flatbreads on sheet then put them in the oven to crisp up for 5 min
-Grab a pan & melt 1 TBSP butter ,Add garlic powder, remaining Italian Seasoning, and 1 TBSP flour
-Whisk constantly until lightly browned, 30 seconds. Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in cream cheese and ½ cup water until melted and combined.
-Once roasted garlic is done, carefully transfer cloves to a cutting board and roughly chop. Evenly top toasted flatbreads with white sauce, roasted garlic, and veggies. Sprinkle with mozzarella.
Return flatbreads to oven until mozzarella malts, 2-3 minutes.

Before I started working with @gav_pratt  I never really understood why he made me focus on breathing through my nose during workouts. After asking him and doing research, here are some of the facts that I’ve found out.

Nasal breathing during cardio is great for athletes because it helps to increase the amount of oxygen that is taken in and utilized by the body. When you breathe through your nose, the air is filtered, humidified, and warmed before it enters the lungs. This helps to improve the efficiency of gas exchange in the lungs, which means that more oxygen is absorbed into the bloodstream with each breath. 

Additionally, nasal breathing helps to regulate the amount of carbon dioxide in the body. When you breathe through

There are several benefits of nasal breathing for athletes during cardio:

1. Increased oxygen uptake: Nasal breathing allows the body to take in more oxygen with each breath, improving the efficiency of gas exchange in the lungs.

2. Reduced fatigue: By increasing oxygen uptake, nasal breathing helps to reduce fatigue during exercise, allowing athletes to perform at a higher level for longer.

3. Improved endurance: Nasal breathing can help to improve endurance by reducing the amount of energy expended during exercise.

4. Better recovery

The purpose of performing trap bar deadlifts with a deficit in MMA training can have several benefits:

1. Increased strength and power: Trap bar deadlifts work the entire posterior chain, including the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. By performing them with a deficit (standing on a platform or plates), you increase the range of motion and challenge the muscles even further, leading to enhanced strength and power in those areas.

2. Improved explosiveness and athleticism: Deadlifts are a compound exercise that require full-body coordination and explosiveness. By incorporating deficit trap bar deadlifts into MMA training, fighters can enhance their explosiveness and athletic performance, which can be beneficial in generating explosive strikes, takedowns, and movements in the octagon.

3. Injury prevention and core stability: Deadlifts, especially with a trap bar, engage the core muscles, improving stability and reducing the risk of injury. The deficits further challenge the core by requiring greater stability and control, which can help fighters maintain proper form and stability during dynamic movements in MMA.

4. Grip strength and conditioning: Grip strength is crucial in MMA for controlling opponents, securing holds, and maintaining control during grappling exchanges. Trap bar deadlifts with a deficit put additional stress on the grip, helping to improve grip strength and endurance, which can be advantageous during fights.

Overall, incorporating deficit trap bar deadlifts into MMA training can improve strength, explosiveness, athleticism, injury prevention, core stability, and grip strength, all of which are essential for success in the sport.

Taking OPTi greens, OPTi reds, and micro factor mid-flight can offer several benefits to support your well-being during travel. Here are some reasons why I choose to take these on-the-go supplements:

1. Nutrient Boost: Traveling can sometimes disrupt our regular eating patterns, making it challenging to consume a balanced diet. OPTi greens, OPTi reds, and micro factor provide a concentrated blend of essential nutrients, including vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. Taking them mid-flight ensures you’re getting a nutrient boost to support your overall health and fill potential nutrient gaps.

2. Immune Support: Airports and airplanes can be breeding grounds for germs, increasing the risk of catching a cold or other illnesses. OPTi greens, OPTi reds, and micro factor contain immune-boosting nutrients like vitamin C, which can help strengthen your immune system and support your body’s defense against infections.

3. Energy and Vitality: Long flights and jet lag can leave you feeling tired and drained. OPTi greens and OPTi reds are designed to enhance energy levels, while micro factor provides essential nutrients that support overall vitality. Taking these supplements mid-flight can help combat fatigue and keep you feeling more energized during and after your journey.

4. Antioxidant Protection: Flying exposes you to increased oxidative stress due to altitude, recycled air, and radiation. OPTi reds and micro factor are rich in antioxidants, which help neutralize harmful free radicals and reduce inflammation. This antioxidant protection can support your overall well-being during and after your flight.

I have to admit, I’m not a big fan of general fitness. That’s why I’ve turned to mixed martial arts - it offers a fresh and ever-changing training experience. Even though you may practice the same techniques, each session brings a unique drilling style or live roll that keeps things exciting, and that’s why I’m so passionate about it. On the other hand, going to the weight room feels monotonous to me. The repetitive motions and mindless reps make me loathe lifting. However, don’t get me wrong, I understand the importance of weight training and how it can lead to increased strength and stamina. To stay consistent in the weight room, I rely on my personal trainer. I’ve known him for years, and his engaging conversations and motivating attitude make the gym much more enjoyable. Thanks to his guidance, I’ve been able to see significant progress in my body’s strength, balance, and stamina. Finding the right personal trainer for your needs is absolutely crucial. Look for someone who not only pushes you physically but also educates and motivates you. They should be able to call you out on any excuses or obstacles you may face. With the right trainer by your side, you’ll be well on your way to achieving your fitness goals.

Shout out to @strong_a.f for being an exceptional personal trainer

Yesterday, I had the amazing experience of scoring my second ace! @denverdoug and I were playing at Johnny Robert’s in Arvada, which is a fantastic course known for its ace runs. It was an incredible day because we encountered several groups who had also been collecting aces on the course. Even my playing partner managed to get one on hole 4!

Just before I took my shot, there was a group behind us who were jokingly saying they would cover us and get an ace on the previous hole. It was all in good fun and it led to the commentary in the video. If you watch the video closely, you can actually see them jumping for joy in the distance as I successfully put my disc in the basket.

Experiencing or witnessing an ace in disc golf is one of the most thrilling feelings. It doesn’t matter if you’re the one getting the ace or just watching it happen, you understand how difficult it is to achieve and all you can do is share in the joy.

Hole 11 at Johnny Robert’s will forever be etched in my memory, along with my favorite putter, the Crazy Tuff Luna. If you’re interested in getting one for yourself, I’ve included a link to them in my bio.

#ace #discraft #discgolf #discgolflife #discgolfeveryday

Monday’s strength and conditioning session focused on enhancing explosion, power, and endurance for MMA. 

It can be challenging to walk into the gym knowing that you have an intense workout ahead, rated at an 8 out of 10 difficulty. However, it’s important to remember that you can’t negotiate with yourself anymore. Simply show up and take things one step at a time. It may not be enjoyable, and it definitely won’t be easy. You’ll likely feel exhausted throughout the entire session. But remember, this is how you grow and progress. It’s during those moments when you don’t feel like showing up, but you still do, that you truly push yourself to the next level. 

After completing the workout, it’s crucial to fuel your body with fast-acting carbohydrates and protein to aid in recovery. Personally, my go-to post-training supplements are Ignition and Phormula 1. I like to dry scoop them right after my training session to support my body’s recovery process.

Win the day, win the week. Win enough weeks, win the month. Consecutively win the month, win the year.

Jordan Peterson said in an interview: “If you want to discover something about yourself, take a moment to sit on your bed at night and reflect on this question: ‘What’s one thing I’m doing wrong, that I know I’m doing wrong? That I could fix. That I would fix.’ By meditating on this question, you’ll find the answer you seek.”

This quote has had a profound impact on me, prompting me to take action and make positive changes in my life. I’ve embraced the challenge of stepping out of my comfort zone and engaging in activities I wouldn’t normally do. This includes dedicating time to reading, taking classes, expanding my education, and establishing a healthy morning routine that involves going for a walk as soon as I wake up.

While I understand that a mere seven days may not completely transform my lifestyle or mindset, I view it as a significant starting point on my journey of self-improvement. I am committed to continuing in the right direction, making positive changes that will benefit my future self.

In addition to these personal growth efforts, I’ve also embarked on the 75 Hard program. For the past week, I’ve been diligently documenting my goals and daily tasks to optimize my schedule and increase efficiency. This structured approach has allowed me to make consistent progress towards my future aspirations.

I will say that with each passing day, I feel a greater sense of well-being and improvement since embarking on this journey. The positive changes I’m implementing are already making a noticeable impact on my overall well-being, and I’m eagerly looking forward to the continued path of self-improvement ahead.
